This implementation uses two stacks, one to hold items waiting to be processed and another to hold items that have been processed.
```python
class Queue:
    def __init__(self):
        self.in_stack = []
        self.out_stack = []

    def enqueue(self, item):
        self.in_stack.append(item)

    def dequeue(self):
        if not self.out_stack:
            while self.in_stack:
                self.out_stack.append(self.in_stack.pop())
        return self.out_stack.pop()
```

To enqueue an item, we simply append it to the in_stack. To dequeue an item, we first check if there are any items in the out_stack. If not, we transfer all the items from the in_stack to the out_stack until it is empty. Then, we pop and return the last item added to the out_stack.

